}, {\"ngram\": \"agreement\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 667}, {\"ngram\": \"muted displeasure\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 689}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And therein lies the nightmare.Breaking Away: The Cas...McMaken, RyanCheck Amazon for Pricing.\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 786, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the nightmare\", \"from\": 709, \"to\": 722}, {\"ngram\": \"The Cas...McMaken\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 755}, {\"ngram\": \"RyanCheck Amazon\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 773}, {\"ngram\": \"Pricing\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 785}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not in the debased performance, but rather in the chic acceptance.\", \"from\": 788, \"to\": 854, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the debased performance\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 818}, {\"ngram\": \"the chic acceptance\", \"from\": 834, \"to\": 853}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even a Caligula would have been embarrassed.\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 862, \"end\": 870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caligula\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7727150305603593e-25, \"text\": \"Caligula\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caligula\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caligula\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His depravity would never have dreamt of mocking the firmament of Roman gods, or dislodging the foundations of the Roman Imperium.\", \"from\": 900, \"to\": 1030, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 966, \"end\": 976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Religion_in_ancient_Rome\", \"score\": 0.999999999733518, \"rank\": 2.6638371302865067e-10, \"text\": \"Roman gods\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Religion_in_ancient_Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Religion_in_ancient_Rome\"}, {\"begin\": 1015, \"end\": 1020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"score\": 0.9936584519632216, \"rank\": 0.005943588052831197, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\"}, {\"begin\": 1021, \"end\": 1029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imperium\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9426806782473756e-22, \"text\": \"Imperium\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imperium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imperium\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His depravity\", \"from\": 900, \"to\": 913}, {\"ngram\": \"the firmament\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 962}, {\"ngram\": \"the foundations\", \"from\": 992, \"to\": 1007}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than a few were probably haunted by the premonitory verses of Yeats in his \\\"The Second Coming\\\": Turning and turning in the widening gyreThe falcon cannot hear the falconer;Things fall apart; the centre cannot hold;Mere anarchy is loosed upon the world,The blood-dimmed tide is loosed, and everywhereThe ceremony of innocence is drowned;The best lack all conviction, while the worstAre full of passionate intensity.\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1452, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the premonitory verses\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1095}, {\"ngram\": \"Yeats\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1104}, {\"ngram\": \"his \\\"The Second Coming\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1130}, {\"ngram\": \"the widening gyreThe falcon\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1183}, {\"ngram\": \"the falconer;Things\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1215}, {\"ngram\": \"the centre\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1238}, {\"ngram\": \"anarchy\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1263}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1279, \"to\": 1288}, {\"ngram\": \"The blood-dimmed tide\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1310}, {\"ngram\": \"everywhereThe ceremony\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1348}, {\"ngram\": \"innocence\", \"from\": 1352, \"to\": 1361}, {\"ngram\": \"drowned;The best lack\", \"from\": 1365, \"to\": 1386}, {\"ngram\": \"passionate intensity\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1450}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The tragedy was not the outrageous blasphemy.\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1499, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The tragedy\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1465}, {\"ngram\": \"the outrageous blasphemy\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1498}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the absence of howling outrage.\", \"from\": 1500, \"to\": 1538, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the absence\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1518}, {\"ngram\": \"outrage\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1537}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No such supine reaction would have met such an attack on Islam.\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1602, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No such supine reaction\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1562}, {\"ngram\": \"such an attack\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"Islam\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1601}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For all its wild aberrations, it does not lack the manliness of instantaneous fury.\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1686, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all its wild aberrations\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1631}, {\"ngram\": \"the manliness\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1663}, {\"ngram\": \"instantaneous fury\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1685}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not so the once chest-thumping Catholicism of the saints and martyrs.\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1756, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Not so the once chest-thumping Catholicism\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1729}, {\"ngram\": \"the saints\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1743}, {\"ngram\": \"martyrs\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1755}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sixty years ago, that millennial Catholic trademark was thought embarrassing for a Church in a hurry to make friends with the world.\", \"from\": 1757, \"to\": 1889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1790, \"end\": 1798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.452063760300906e-15, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://